(1696, 160264, '2012-10-14 16:08:11', '"In the CA1 area of the hippocampus, somatostatin is expressed in O-LM [oriens--lacunosum-moleculare] cells\n(Freund and Buzsaki, 1996), in hippocampal-septal cells\n(Gulyas et al., 2003), and in bistratified cells (Klausberger\net al., 2004). The highest numbers of somatostatin-positive\ncells are seen in the stratum oriens, which likely\ncorrespond to the O-LM cells."', 'p 561 right', 'data', NULL, NULL),
