(2086, 160556, '2012-10-14 16:08:17', '"One out of four tested cells was immunopositive (Fig. 10) for the proCCK[cholecystokinin]\npolypeptide (Morino et al. 1994), as were scattered cells in\nall layers, particularly at the border of str. radiatum and\nlacunosummoleculare.  Most pyramidal cells were also\nimmunopositive (Morino et al. 1994) in a perinuclear pattern\ncorresponding to the Golgi apparatus (Fig. 10), but the somatostatin immunoreactive neurones were immunonegative\nfor proCCK."', 'p 104 right', 'data', NULL, NULL),
