(2164, 160620, '2012-10-14 16:08:19', '"In CA1, previous studies have described a pronounced sag and spike frequency\nadaptation in three classes of interneurons: OLM [oriens--lacunosum-moleculare] cells (Ali and\nThomson, 1998), a CCK[cholecystokinin]-immunopositive Schaffer-associated\ncell, and a CCK-immunopositive quadrilaminar cell (with soma\nat the SR[stratum radiatum]/SLM[stratum lacunosum-moleculare] border and axon arborizing in SO [stratum oriens], SP [stratum pyramidale], SR, and\nSLM) (Pawelzik et al., 2002)."', 'p 7335 left bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
