(2528, 160950, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2529, 160950, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2530, 160952, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"All the VIP cells projecting to the O/A border\n(N = 18) were found to be immunopositive for calretinin\n(Fig. 6). Indeed, a band of calretinin positive\naxon terminals can be seen at the O/A border of\nthe CA1 subfield (not illustrated), confirming the\nexistence of a unique interneuron type which\nspecifically targets this sublayer and co-localizes VIP\nand calretinin."', 'p 311 left top', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2531, 160952, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2532, 160952, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2533, 160954, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"Among the [vasoactive intestinal polypeptide-positive CA1] cells projecting to stratum radiatum\nand having radial dendrites spanning all layers, calretinin-\npositive (N = 5) and negative (N = 7) cells were\nalso found in the CA 1 region. However from the 15\nVIP-positive cells with dendrites in the stratum lacunosum-\nmoleculare 14 were found to be negative for\ncalretinin. Similarly all the examined VIP-positive\nbasket cells (N =9) proved to lack calretininimmunoreactivity\n(Fig. 7)."', 'p 311 left top', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2534, 160954, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2535, 160954, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2536, 160956, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"From the 76 VIP[vasoactive intestinal polypeptide]-containing interneurons\nin the CA1 region 19 showed CCK [cholecystokinin]\nimmunoreactivity (25%), which is similar to the\nearlier findings. 21  We characterized the CCK-positive\nand negative VIP cells according to the morphological\ncriteria mentioned above. All but one of the\nVIP-positive basket cells (N = 14) were immunoreactive\nfor CCK (Fig. 7), while neither VIP-positive\ncells projecting to the O/A border (N = 11) nor those\nwith dendrites restricted to stratum lacunosummoleculare\n(N = 8) showed CCK immunopositivity.\nA small proportion (six out of 43) of the remaining,\nsmall, VIP-containing cells with axon projecting\nto stratum radiatum were immunoreactive for\nCCK."', 'p 311 left bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2537, 160956, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2538, 160956, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2539, 160958, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"The pattern of calbindin D-28k and\nparvalbumin immunostaining was identical to that\ndescribed earlier (2, 10, 47)  Briefly, calbindin D-28k\nstained the granule cells of the dentate gyrus, the CAI\npyramidal cells and scattered interneurons in the\ndendritic region of the principal cells."', 'p 311 right top', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2540, 160958, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2541, 160958, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2542, 160960, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"From 210 VIP-immunoreactive interneurons in\nCAI, 208 were negative for calbindin D-28k (Fig. 8C,\nD) whereas none of the 44 VIP-containing neurons in\nCA3 showed calbindin D-28k immunofluorescence."', 'p 311 right mid', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2543, 160960, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2544, 160960, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2545, 160962, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"In the case of parvalbumin-VIP co-localization, only\nthose VIP cells within or close to stratum pyramidale\nwere examined, since parvalbumin cells are absent in\nother layers. Thus, all VIP-positive cells in the distal\npart of stratum radiatum or in stratum lacunosummoleculare\nare considered parvalbumin-negative by\ntheir position. None of the 136 VIP-immunopositive\ncells near stratum pyramidale in CA1 and the 36 in\nCA3 showed parvalbumin immunofluorescence\n(Fig. 8E, F). In addition, 15 large multipolar VIPpositive\nbasket cells were selected from different\nsections, but those were also negative for parvalburain.\nThis finding demonstrates that there is a basket\ncell type different from those containing parvalbumin\nbut which is characterized by the coexistence of VIP\nand CCK."', 'p 311 right bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2546, 160962, '2012-10-14 16:08:25', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2547, 160962, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2548, 160964, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"Cells projecting to the O/A border always\ncontained calretinin, those with the axon in stratum\nradiatum and dendrites in stratum lacunosum-moleculare\nwere negative for calretinin similar to VIP-containing\nbasket cells, whereas cells with the axon in\nstratum radiatum and dendrites spanning all layers\nco-localized calretinin in 40% of the cases."', 'p 312 left top', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2549, 160964, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2550, 160964, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2551, 160966, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"CCK was\nco-localized with VIP in basket cells, but was absent\nfrom the other types (except for a few cells with the\naxon in stratum radiatum and dendrites in all layers.)\nCalbindin and parvalbumin showed no coexistence\nwith VIP. Co-localization with GABA, revealed\n100% coexistence with VIP."', 'p 312 left top', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2552, 160966, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2553, 160966, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2554, 160968, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"In\nthe CAI subfield, bistratified cells were shown to be\nlinked to the Schaffer collateral system confining the\nvast majority of their dendrites to stratum radiatum\nand oriens. 8 Many of the calretinin-containing cells\n(which are not immunoreactive for VIP [vasoactive intestinal polypeptide]) have similar\ndendritic trees.14"', 'p 312 left bot', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2555, 160968, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2556, 160968, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL),
(2557, 160970, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"The third subpopulation of VIP[vasoactive intestinal polypeptide]-containing cells\nare basket cells as identified by their large multipolar\nsoma and the pericellular arrays of boutons they form\naround pyramidal cell bodies and possibly also\naround other interneurons in stratum pyramidale.\nThis way of termination resembles the previously\nwell characterized parvalbumin-containing basket\ncells. 18.23 However, no coexistence was found between\nVIP and parvalbumin in the present study, thus,\nVIP-positive basket cells represent a new, anatomically\nvery similar, but neurochemically different basket\ncell type, which also contains CCK [cholecystokinin]."', 'p 313 left mid', 'data', NULL, NULL),
(2558, 160970, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', '"[1] For single immunostaining rabbit anti-calretinin\n(1:5000), 36 or rabbit anti-VIP (1: 10,000) (13) or rabbit anti-\nCCK (1:3000) (13) or monoclonal mouse anti-GABA (1:50) (45)\nwere used as primary antisera.  [2] For fluorescent double-staining the following mixtures\nof antisera were used: rabbit anti-VIP (1 : 5000) and mouse\nanti-calbindin (1:2000) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and mouse\nanti-parvalbumin (1:500) (10) or rabbit anti-VIP and\nmouse anti-GABA (1:30). (45)"', 'p 300 left bot, right mid', 'protocol', NULL, NULL),
(2559, 160970, '2012-10-14 16:08:26', NULL, NULL, 'animal', NULL, NULL);
