(2635, 161020, '2012-10-14 16:08:27', '"In area CA1, the pattern of PV-LI [parvalbumin-like immunoreactivty] is\nstrikingly dissimilar from the pattern of CaBP-LI [calbindin-like immunoreactivity] in that\nPV-LI is present almost exclusively in cells whose somata\nare in strata pyramidale and oriens or at the oriens/alveus\nborder (Fig. 7). Like CAI pyramidal cells, these PV-immunoreactive\ncells send dendrites into strata oriens and radiatum. Unlike CA1 pyramidal cells, the dendrites of PVpositive\ncells are thin, beaded, and aspinous (assuming that\nPV-immunoreactivity reveals dendritic morpohology accurately\nby filling the entire cytoplasm with DAB) and they\nform an axosomatic plexus around the pyramidal cells."', 'p 193 right', 'data', NULL, NULL),
