(2806, 160743, '2012-10-14 16:08:30', '"Of 13 recorded CCK-IR basket cells in the CA1, 6 had their somata in the SP (Fig. 6F, Table 1), 3 in the SO (Fig. 6A), and 4 in the SR. Two of the SR basket cells were located close to the SR/SLM border (Fig. 7). The main axonal arborisations of these cells were con?ned to the SP, where they formed perisomatic basket-like arrangements, although some branches rami?ed in the proximal SR and SO (Figs. 6, 7). Portions of the large axonal branches of these cells were myelinated. The vertical dendritic trees of the SP basket cells rami?ed primarily in the SO and SR and, like those of PV-IR basket cells, extended into the SLM and alveus (Tables 1, 2)."', 'p 358 left top', 'data', NULL, NULL),
