(2844, 160110, '2012-10-14 16:08:31', '"Pyramidal cells in the compact layer of stratum pyramidale [of CA1] next to stratum\nradiatum are weakly immunopositive for calbindin and\nare smaller than pyramidal cells more loosely arranged\ntowards stratum oriens, which are calbindin immunonegative\n(Baimbridge & Miller, 1982)."', 'p 11 left', 'data', NULL, NULL),
