(2931, 160638, '2012-10-14 16:08:32', '"The data here show that CB[calbindin]- and Prox1-positive GCs [granule cells] exist in the\nCA3 region of the normal, healthy rat. CA3 GCs are similar to DG [dentate gyrus]\nGCs in their somato-dendritic morphology, intrinsic electrophysiological\nproperties, and the MF[mossy fiber]-like nature of their axons,\nand they are present in numbers that are comparable to the rarer\nGABA[gamma aminobutyric acid]ergic cell types."', 'p 8303 right botg', 'data', NULL, NULL),
