(1008, 112, '2012-10-14 16:07:27', 'DG (-)3000 molecular layer perforant path associated-neurogliaform (MOPP-NGF) cells', 'MOPP (-)3000', 'active', 'Status: \r\nActive.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current mergers proposed.\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\nnone\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nThe VIP-positive neurons are speculated to be interneuron specific.  If this is ever proven, then these cells should be separated from the MOPP-NGF cells.\r\n'),
(1009, 114, '2012-10-14 16:07:27', 'DG (-)2322 hilar commissural-associational pathway related (HICAP) neurons', 'HICAP (-)2322', 'active', 'Han et al., 1993: young adult female Wistar rats\r\n \r\nMott et al., 1997: male 16-30 d-old Sprague Dawley rats\r\n\r\nPrimary literature moved to the front of the packet.\r\n\r\nNotes about animals added.\r\n\r\nAfter a thorough search, no data could be found for perisomatic contact\r\nwith granule cells.\r\n\r\nInterpretations are unchanged.'),
