(1026, 122, '2012-10-14 16:07:27', 'DG (-)1333p-CA3 01111 hilar interneurons with collaterals in all layers (HICAL)', 'HICAL (-)1333p', 'active', 'Status:\r\nNew. Active.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\nDG (-)2333 apiny hilar interneurons\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nN = 3 cells are spiny, N = 4 cells are aspiny.\r\n\r\nBoth spiny and aspiny cells are able to form basket-like bouton arrays on GC somata and somata of other hilar neurons.\r\n\r\nThe youngest rats may be adolescents.'),
(1027, 113, '2012-10-14 16:07:27', 'DG (-)2333 aspiny hilar interneurons', 'Aspiny hilar (-)2333', 'active', 'Status:\r\nNew. Active.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\nDG (-)2333p-CA3 01111 hilar interneuron with collaterals in all layers (HICAL)\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nN = 4.\r\n\r\nA:DG:SMo and A:CA3c are less than 15%.\r\n\r\nD:CA3c is less than 15%.\r\n\r\nYoungest rats may be adolescents.\r\n\r\nAspiny.\r\n\r\nA:SG form basket-like boutons around GC somata.  A:H form basket-like bouton arrays around somata.  These cells are the inverse of DG (-)2232 basket cells.  These have clear presence in SMi and H, and minimal in SG.'),
