(2042, 216, '2012-10-14 16:07:27', 'CA3 (-)03333p-DG 0003 interneuron specific-3 (IS-3) neurons', 'Interneuron spec-3 (-)03333p', 'active', 'Status: new\r\nActive.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\nDG (-)0003 interneuron specific-3 neurons (suspended)\r\n\r\nNotes: This class has been reinterpreted with multiple layers CA3:SR_SL_SP_SO enclosed by the hilus, which are not delineated by the authors.  The ordering from top to bottom is unknown.\r\n\r\nIf CA3c is ever separated out as a separate parcel, this class will be affected.\r\n\r\nDirected to Hájos paper by Freund and Buzsáki, who tried to draw parallels between IS-3 neurons in CA1, CA3, and DG, and, therefore, declared dendrites in all layers and axons only in the hilus (typo in F&B Table 2 - "IS-2" should be "IS-3").  Since this interpretation is counter to the single figure from Hájos, Freund and Buzsáki citations have been omitted from this packet.\r\n\r\nA citation search yielded no further information.\r\n\r\nA neuron that had been previously interpreted as CA3 (-)03000 stratum radiatum has now been absorbed into this class.\r\n\r\nN = 3.\r\n\r\n13 out of 166 VIP+ cells (8%) split across this packet and DG (-)0003.\r\n\r\nFormed a small number of en passant or drumstick-like boutons.\r\n\r\nAxons difficult to follow once in DG:H.\r\n\r\nNon-principal cell specific targeting with multiple contacts on somata and dendrites.'),
