(4028, 443, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0300 Schaffer collateral associated-stratum radiatum-calbindin (SCA-SR-CB) neurons', 'Radiatum (-)0300', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n  - This packet is a result of a merger between CA1 0300 SCA-SR and CA1\r\n    0300 calbindin SR.\r\n  - Rejected merger with CA1 (-)1300 SLM-SR due to strength of A:SLM. \r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nPossible future subclasses based on expression of chemical markers (SCA-SR packet appears to be CCK+; CB-SR packet is CB+)\r\n\r\nCA1 0300 SCA-SR notes:\r\n- Language of various authors indicates that dendrites can enter SLM or SO, but they do so "rarely" (Freund & Buzsaki, 1996).\r\n- SCA-ADI 2311 packet also exists\r\n- SCA 2300 packet no longer exists.  It was n=1 and that cell (Vida 1998) is now included here (same cell as Vida 2010, which was already in this packet)\r\n- SCA neurons in this packet are CCK+ (Cope 2002; Pawelzik 2002)\r\n\r\nCA1 0300 calbindin SR notes:\r\n- Other CA1 calbindin packets exist:\r\n    * CA1 calbindin 3100\r\n    * CA1 calbindin 0303\r\n    * CA1 calbindin-IS-1 0302\r\n    * CA1 calbindin-SO-SO 0003\r\n- CA3 calbindin packets also exist.'),
(4031, 449, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0102 stratum oriens-targeting interneuron specific-1 (SO IS-1) neurons', 'Interneuron spec-6 (-)0102', 'active', 'Status:\r\nActive.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis packet is a merger of CA1 (-)0102 IS-I and CA1 (-)0112 IS-I\r\n\r\nPrevious merger of CA1 (-)0102 IS-I with CA1 0103 O-R (aka oriens-bistratified) was rejected due to the lack of axonal evidence in SO.  Namely, even with six consecutive 80 ľm sections, axons were not significantly present.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nPacket now uses original (Gulyás) evidence rather than the Freund & Buzsáki review.\r\n\r\nAccording to Gulyás, the CR interneurons in this packet innervate mostly if not exclusively other GABAergic neurons via multiple synapses'),
(4033, 452, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0003 calbindin-stratum oriens startum oriens (CB-SOSO) neurons', 'Oriens-oriens (-)0003', 'active', 'This class is a merger of:\r\n- CA1 calbindin 0003\r\n- CA1 SO-SO 0003\r\n\r\n\r\nPossible future subclasses based on markers (calbindin, CCK) or \r\nelectrophysiology (SO-SO are FS, calbindin unknown)\r\n\r\n"Subcover" pages within contain notes from the original \r\n(pre-merger) classes.'),
(4035, 448, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0113p-SUB 111 trilaminar horizontal-irens retrohippocampal projecting-double projecting-oriens radiatum (TH-ORP-DP-OR) neurons', 'Double proj (-)0113p', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nMerger approved between four classes: CA1 0113 ORP, CA1 0113 DP, CA1 0113 trilaminar horizontal, CA1 0113 O-R\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n\r\nProjection to SUB - the ORP-DP-trilaminar horizontal packet has been approved with [A:SUB:SM_SP_PL] (horiz trilaminar cells match this; ORP cells have clear axons in SUB:SM_SP and borderline axons in PL; DP cell axons could not be followed to terminals so could not be traced further than SUB:SP).  The O-R 0113 packet has clear axons in SUB:SP_PL, and Losonczy admits that the axons may have been severely truncated.\r\n\r\nSeptal projection - potential for subclasses.  DP cells project into the \r\nseptal area and ORP cells do not.  Unknown for trilaminar-horizontal and O-R.\r\n\r\nTargets - according to Somogyi (2010), up to half of the postsynaptic targets of trilaminar (horizontal) cells are other interneurons.  Possible potential for subclasses.\r\n\r\n*Note:  packet needs slight updating.  Not all papers contain a highlighted methods section*\r\n'),
(4036, 423, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)2232 axo-axonic (AA) neurons', 'Axo-axonic (-)2232', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    Merger with CA1 2223 basket cells REVOKED due to the issue of target\r\n        specificity.  Axo-axonic cells exclusively target pyramidal cells\r\n        while basket cells are also known to target other interneurons.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nExclusive innervation of pyramidal cells; axo-axonic cells do NOT connect with other interneurons\r\n\r\nHippocampome rules enacted:\r\n- Rule 4, Section 3, Subsection ii, Clause 3 - perisomatic axonal targeting interpreted as PCL\r\n- Rule 4, Section 3, Subsection iii, Clause 1 - extended interpretation of SP in apical and basal directions\r\n\r\nOriginal evidence added (Somogyi 1977; Li et al., 1992)'),
(4038, 451, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0012 axo-axonic horizontal (AA horz) neurons', 'Axo-axonic horiz (-)0012', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    Merger with CA1 (-)0012 basket-FS-PTI cells revoked\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nAxons exclusively target the axon initial segment of CA1 pyramidal cells (and, unlike basket cells, do not target other interneurons)\r\n\r\nHippocampome rules enacted:\r\n- Rule 4, Section 3, Subsection ii, Clause 3 - perisomatic axonal targeting interpreted as PCL\r\n- Rule 4, Section 3, Subsection iii, Clause 1 - extended interpretation of SP in apical and basal directions'),
(4039, 450, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0012 basket cells-fast spiking perisomatic targeting interneurons (BC-FSPTI)', 'Perisomatic target (-)0012', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n- Merger REVOKED between CA1 (-)0012 axo-axonic and CA1 0012 basket cells due to target specificity.  Axo-axonic cells exclusively target pyramidal cells; basket cells also target interneurons.\r\n\r\n- The Zemankovics CA1 (-)0012 FS PTI cells are merged into this packet even though the authors could not distinguish between axo-axonic and basket cells\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nTarget soma and proximal dendrites of CA1 pyramidal cells and other interneurons.\r\n\r\nHippocampome rules enacted:\r\n- Rule 4, Section 3, Subsection ii, Clause 3 - perisomatic axonal targeting interpreted as PCL\r\n- Rule 4, Section 3, Subsection iii, Clause 1 - extended interpretation of SP in apical and basal directions'),
(4041, 438, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)0313p-SUB 001 enkephalin-expressing (ENK) cells', 'Enkephalin (-)0313p', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    No mergers currently proposed.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\n- inhibitory because GABAergic (Fuentealba et al., 2008)\r\n- interneuron specific:\r\n      - 57% of CA1 targets and 100% of SUB targets were interneurons\r\n        (Fuentealba 2008)\r\n      - up to half the targets are other interneurons (Somogyi 2010)\r\n- 11.3% (7/62) of hippocampo-subicular nonpyramidal projection cells were ENK-immunopositive\r\n- Fuentealba paper refers to these cells as a "population," though only one cell could be positively identified\r\n\r\n'),
