(4054, 402, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (+)2201 pyramidal-like principal-radiatum giant cells (PLP-RGC)', 'Radiatum giant (+)2201', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nMerger of CA1 (+)2221 pyramidal-like principal (PLP) cells and CA1 (+)2201 radiatum giant cells (RGC).\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nCA1 PLP 2221 packet contains unverified connections to SUB and EC.\r\n\r\nThere is no CLEAR evidence for dendrites in SP in either packet.\r\n\r\nThe PLP packet text mentions "soma located approximately 50 microm from \r\nthe SP."  Based on the scale bar, basal dendrites are located near the \r\nSR/SP border and just within fuzzy boundaries for the principal layer.\r\n\r\nThe RGC packet has Gulyas (1998) Fig 2, which shows the soma of cells 1-3\r\nalso located about 50-100 microm from the SR/SP border, and it looks like\r\nthe dendrites have similar extent to PLP cells.  Cell #5 does not have \r\ndendrites near SP, so it likely will NOT fit into a 2221 interpretation.\r\n\r\nIn the PLP packet, Poolos et al declare PLPs to be a subset of RGCs based\r\non bifurcation patterns of the apical dendrites and soma shape.  However, there appears to be no current basis for hippocampome subclasses.'),
(4055, 420, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)2233 oriens-alveus (O-A) neurons', 'Oriens-alveus (-)2233', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n    Previous (outdated) O-A 2233 packet was suspended (see below).\r\n    It was split into this active packet and an 0233 suspended packet.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    No current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nTarget pyramidal cells (dendrites, somata, AND axon initial segment) as well as other interneurons (dendrites).\r\n\r\nThe Lacaille papers were previously considered inadequate for the creation of an active cell class.  That decision was revisited.\r\n\r\nAccording to the 1990 paper, 50% of the cells have D:SLM and 50% do not.  Unfortunately, the extent of the dendrites in the latter case is unclear and the packet is suspended.  See also:  CA1 0233 O-A.\r\n\r\nLacaille 1987 mentions other (unspecified) morphologies and contains some troubling/vague phrasing, but there is enough evidence in their text to push this through as a class.\r\n\r\nLacaille 1990 does not contain axonal information and is in a separate species (rat, rather than guinea pig), BUT since the first author is the same and he makes the statement that these cells have "similar morphology," the information is considered linked and is used.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPacket contains papers with abundant electrophysiology data.'),
(4056, 419, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)2300 stratum radiatum-targeting interneuron specific-1 (SR IS-1) neurons', 'Interneuron spec-5 (-)2300', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n- This packet is a result of a merger between CA1 2300 IS-1 and 2310 IS-1\r\n- Unable to merge with CA1 SCA 2300 because of target specificiy.\r\n   \r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nThis merger is a combination of two n=1 classes.\r\n\r\nIn this merger case, contrary to the usual hippocampome rule, axons in SP are NOT counted because somatic targeting in the principal layer is less relevant for IS interneurons (GAA).\r\n\r\n'),
