(4068, 431, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)1113p-SUB 111 oriens-bistratified cells (O-BiC)', 'Bistratified proj (-)1113p', 'active', 'Status: new\r\nActive.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\n- CA1 (-)0113p-SUB 111 TH-ORP-DP-OR (active).  Packet contains Losonczy (2002) Fig 5b, as well as "classic" oriens-bistratified cells (aka O-R cells) first described by Maccaferri (2000).\r\n- CA2 (-)0003p-CA3 00003-CA1 0003-SUB 010 (suspended).  Packet contains Losonczy (2002) Fig 5d.\r\n\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nAxonal arbor is very wide and extent of projections is somewhat unclear.  The subject is not discussed in Katona (1999) and Losonczy (2002) admit that the arbor was likely "severly truncated" due to slicing.\r\n\r\nThe cell in Losonczy''s Fig 5a does not project to CA3, though the authors speculate that 40% of oriens-bistratified cells project both there and to the subiculum.\r\n\r\nElectrophysiology and chemical marker (SST+) data in Losonczy (2002).'),
(4069, 435, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'CA1 (-)1002 oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) neurons', 'O-LM (-)1002', 'active', 'Status: Active.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis packet is a merger of CA1 (-)1002 oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) neurons, CA1 (-)1003 oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) neurons, and CA1 (-)1102 oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) w/o back-projection neurons.\r\n\r\nRelated classes:\r\nCA1 (-)1102 O-LM w/o back-proj neurons (suspended)\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nCA1 (-)1003 oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) neurons and CA1 (-)1102 oriens-lacunosum moleculare (O-LM) w/o back-projection neurons are also being maintained as suspended classes since A:SR and A:SO were very close calls.\r\n\r\nSik (1995) reports that 91.5% of the axon collaterals are in SLM; only 7% are in SO.  According to hippocampome rules, this represents a below-threshold presence.\r\n\r\nAxonal presence in SR is variable but consists mostly of continuing branches, with the exception of McBain''s (1994) Fig 4A.\r\n\r\nAxonal presence in SO is also variable and under threshold.  Unless known connections are reported in the future, this presence will not be counted as per hippocampome rules.\r\n\r\nZemankovics (2010) contains EP data; Losonczy (2002) and Tricoire (2011) contain chemical marker and EP data.\r\n\r\nMGE-derived (Tricoire, 2011).'),
