(5005, 502, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'SUB (+)331p-CA1 1110 pyramidal cells-CA1 projecting (PC-CA1)', 'Pyramidal-CA1 (+)331p', 'active', 'Status:\r\nActive.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nRelated classes:\r\nSUB (+)331-EC 000111 pyramidal neurons (active, need Giorgio approval)\r\n\r\nNotes: A:CA1:SP has been added to the interpretation.\r\n\r\nHarris (2001): Axonal reach into CA1:SP less than 200 microm; regular spiking.\r\n\r\nFinch (1983)(not yet cited): Single collateral reaching CA1 SO.\r\n\r\nKöhler (1985) (not yet cited): labeled fibers apparent in CA1 SM_SO.\r\n\r\nWitter email correspondence: "Menno''s recommendation is that we separate the subicular pyramids into two distinct classes, one projecting to EC and the other to CA1. The logic is weak, but here goes the argument: there''s is enough evidence to define 2 classes based on the input connectivity anyway. The more superficial pyramids (within PC but towards ML) have longer & thinner dendrites that receive input from L3 EC pyramidal cells, and these cells do NOT project to EC. In contrast, the deeper subicular pyramids (within PC but towards PL) do NOT receive EC L3 perforant path projections, and they DO project to EC (L5+6). The less clear cut assumption is that the former subicular pyramids form the (less abundant) back-projection to CA1, and the latter cells do not. The reasoning is that in ALL extra-hippocampal projections subicular neurons exclusively target ONE region and do not collateralize to multiple regions. \r\n\r\nMoreover, the two pyramidal subtypes also correspond to the bursting / regular firing phenotype (but we couldn''t remember which was which without pubmed). The evidence for the above is in Menno''s paper in the subiculum special issue (2006?). Some of the rest they found later and he''s digging out an SfN abstract for us, but he gave me permission to quote him as "personal communication" (this email)."'),
(5006, 504, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'SUB (-)300 parvalbumin-positive (PV) neurons', NULL, 'frozen', NULL),
(6002, 602, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)331131p-DG 1100-SUB 101 pyramidal cells V-dentate gyrus and subiculum projecting (PC V-DG-SUB)', 'Bipolar V (+)331131p', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    No current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nLikely excitatory cells (Gloveli -> GABA negative, projecting, EP characteristics similar to principal cells; van Haeften -> spiny; Canto & Witter -> projecting, "principal," sparsely spiny).\r\n\r\nThe van Haeften et al. paper does not include mention of projection to Sub or DG.  Possibly lost to slicing or possibly outside the scope of their interest.\r\n\r\nWhile this morphology appears in Canto''s 201X MEC preprint, there is no mention of this morphology in the LEC preprint.\r\n\r\nAll references cited herein have been reviewed and included in the appropriate packets EXCEPT for Witter & Wouterlood''s 2002 book, which was received via Interlibrary Loan by CLR on 06-14-11 and determined to contain no additional information relevant to the packet.'),
(6003, 603, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'MEC (+)331111p-DG 1000-CA3 10000-CA2 1000-SUB 111 stellate cells II (SC II)', 'Stellate II (+)331111p', 'active', 'All prior comments have been addressed.\r\n\r\nAxonal presence in CA1 has been removed since it is below 15% and\r\nunsupported by the conclusions of the authors.\r\n\r\nThis packet contains primary literature, in order of primacy from:\r\n	Tamamaki and Nojyo, 1993 (EC layer II stellate cells)\r\n	Canto and Witter, MEC prepreint (EC layer II stellate cells)\r\n	Jones, 1994 (EC layer II type I & II stellate cells)\r\n	Beed et al., 2010, (EC layer II stellate cells)\r\n	Schwartz and Coleman, 1981, (EC layer II stellate cells)\r\n'),
(6005, 604, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)331000p-DG 1000-SUB 101 excitatory II neurons', 'Sub proj II (+)331000p', 'active', 'Status: Active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis class is composed of an amalgam of author-defined classes.\r\nFailed unofficial merger proposals with MEC 331111 stellate II, EC 231000 FOMP, and EC 221100 oblique pyramidal-stellate II.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nSparsely spiny to spiny, projecting -> excitatory.\r\n\r\nPacket was previously approved by all, including GAA.  Since then, the horizontal neuron from the Canto LEC preprint has been added.  It was previously in (-)331000, but that cell should not have been classified as inhibitory.  Note that the (-)331000 packet no longer exists because no axonal information remains; the leftovers from that packet have become (-)220000, which is suspended.\r\n\r\nThe figure of the between pyramidal and stellate cell depicts an axon that dies off in L:VI, which is not substantial enough for an A:VI interpretation. - DWW\r\n\r\nC&W''s LEC description of a pyramidal cell matches 331000.  They also describe a second class (333000) that is n=2 (by itself an insufficient percentage to establish a separate class).  However, since the 333000 class does exist, this evidence is included in that packet. - DWW\r\n\r\nThe Canto MEC pyramidal neuron from Figure 5 was added, even though it has borderline dendrites in VI.\r\n\r\nBorderline:\r\nA:IV (Canto 201X LEC preprint fan -- figure)\r\nA:V (Canto 201X LEC preprint fan -- text)\r\nA:VI (Canto 201X MEC preprint pyramidal)\r\nD:III (Tahvildari 2005 fan; Empson 1995 PLN)'),
(6006, 605, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'MEC (+)313300 complex pyramidal cells III medial (cmplx PC III med)', 'Medial pyramidal III (+)313300', 'active', 'Status: Approved \r\n\r\nMerger status: None being considered\r\n   \r\nNotes:  \r\nExcitatory because they have spiny dendrites.'),
(6007, 606, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'LEC (+)233310 complex pyramidal cells III lateral (cmplx PC III lat)', 'Lateral pyramidal III (+)233310', 'active', 'Status: Active \r\n\r\nMerger status: None being considered\r\n   \r\nNotes:  This cell type was approved when it was in a packet with a total of three references.  Its patterning has not changed.  The packet had to be split because this cell is excitatory and the other two are inhibitory.  The other two cells are in the pyramid-looking III packet.'),
(6008, 607, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)233111 pyramidal cells-multiform cells II (PC-MFC II)', 'Pyramidal II (+)233111', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nnone.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nThis class is excitatory because both citations refer to them as spiny.  In addition, C&W are describing principal cells.'),
(6017, 611, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)223111p-CA1 1000-SUB 100 pyramidal cells III small (PC III sm)', 'Small pyramidal III (+)223111p', 'active', 'Status: Active\r\n\r\nMerger status: None being considered\r\n\r\nNotes: 6/13/12--discussion of text differences in prepreint and published\r\nversions of Canto 2011, Hippocampus, "Cellular properties of Principal \r\nNeurons in the Rat Entorhinal Cortex. II. The Medial Entorhinal Cortex added\r\n(see page 37). No morphology decisions changed.'),
(6018, 612, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)223000 stellate cells III (SC III)', 'Stellate III (+)223000', 'active', 'Status: Active\r\n\r\nMerger status: \r\nRejected merger with EC (+)223200p Pyramidal III due to clear presence of D:IV in pyramidal III and unclear in this class.\r\n   \r\nNotes:  Class is a merger of 223000 Stellate and 223100 Stellate 2, which had weak axonal presence in L4'),
(6019, 613, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'MEC (+)221100 oblique pyramidal cells-stellate cells II (OPC-SC II)', 'Oblique pyramidal II (+)221100', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo current merger proposals.\r\n\r\nFailed unofficial merger proposals with MEC (+)331111p stellate II, EC (+)331000p excitatory II, and EC (+)231000 FOMP.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nA:V less than 15%.\r\n\r\nN = 5.\r\n\r\nSpiny dendrites.'),
(6021, 615, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)220033 pyramidal cells V small (PC V sm)', 'Small pyramidal V (+)220033', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    No current merger proposals\r\n    Merger with 220233 was rejected.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nLikely excitatory cells (Hamam 2000 -> spiny; Hamam 2002 -> projecting, spiny; Canto 2008 -> spiny, projecting; Canto 201X MEC preprint -> projecting, "principal," sparsely spiny).\r\n\r\nCanto & Witter 2008 schematic remains in this packet because the authors cite Hamam in the text.  Evidence for D:IV in this schematic is minimal to threshold.\r\n\r\n6/13/12--discussion of text differences in preprint and published \r\nverstions of  Canto 2011, Hippocampus, Cellular Properties of Principal \r\nNeurons in the Rat Entorhinal Cortex.  II.  The Medial Entorhinal Cortex added(see page 21).  No changes made to original morphology decisions.'),
(6023, 616, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'MEC (+)213330 pyramidal cells V (PC V)', 'Pyramidal V (+)213330', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nRejected merger with LEC (+)113330 multipolar neurons 1 III (MPN 1 III), since these cells have "no main apical dendrite traveling up to the pia" and, for MPN 1 III, "Within LI the diameter of the apical dendritic tree can be up to 400 microm." \r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nLikely excitatory cells (Canto 201X MEC preprint -> "principal," spiny to sparsely spiny).\r\n\r\nQuilichini data moved to another packet.\r\nCanto LEC bipolar V neurons moved to another packet.\r\nCanto 2008 schematic moved to another packet.'),
(6024, 618, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'MEC (+)133100 bipolar neurons III (BPN III)', 'Bipolar III (+)133100', 'active', 'Status: Approved \r\n\r\nMerger status: None being considered\r\n   \r\nNotes:  Borderline\r\n        Axons in LI and LV\r\n        Dend in L1'),
(6025, 619, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'LEC (+)113330 multipolar neurons III lateral (MPN III lat)', 'Lateral multipolar III (+)113330', 'active', 'Status: Approved \r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nRejected merger with MEC (+)213330 pyramidal cells V (PC V), since for these cells "Within LI the diameter of the apical dendritic tree can be up to 400 microm," and PC V have "no main apical dendrite traveling up to the pia."  \r\n   \r\nNotes:  \r\nAxon to the angular bundle.\r\n\r\nExcitatory because dendrites are spiny.\r\n'),
