(6052, 630, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)000023 pyramidal cells-polymorphic cells V/VI (PC-PMC V/VI)', 'Pyramidal V-VI (+)000023', 'active', 'Status: Active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\n    This packet is a result of a merger between MEC 000023 pyramidal VI\r\n    and EC 000023 polymorphic V.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nLikely excitatory cells (Canto 201X MEC preprint -> "sparsely spiny to spiny," projecting; Hamam 2000 -> short spines, projecting).\r\n\r\nNotes on MEC 000023 pyramidal packet:\r\n- dendrites and axons in the white matter\r\n\r\nNotes on EC 000023 polymorphic packet:\r\n- weak evidence on axons\r\n- unclear whether dendrites project to the subiculum or to the presubiculum.  The packet was previously approved by D, C, C, and G with dendritic presence in Sub:SP, but Charise pointed out that because of the position of the cell relative to the angular bundle, the projection could be to the presubiculum.  Notes have been added.'),
(6053, 634, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (-)230000 multipolar inhibitory-basket cells II (MPI-BC II)', 'Basket II (-)230000', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nMerger approved with EC 230000 multipolar inhibitory (MPI) II neurons.\r\nFailed unofficial merger with MEC 333000 type 4 III and EC 233000 MPI 1 III.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nBC synapse somata of stellate II, pyramidal II, and other neurons\r\n\r\nMPI cells are inhibitory, since Germroth describes the cells as nearly spineless, which takes precedence over the fact that they are projecting (axons project to the white matter).\r\n\r\n\r\nStrong potential for future subclasses because of target specificity and because MPIs project to the hippocampus but there is no evidence that baskets do this.'),
