(6078, 628, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'LEC (+)001133 multipolar neurons-2 VI (MPN-2 VI)', 'Multipolar VI (+)001133', 'active', 'Status: active.\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nNo curent mergers proposed\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\nEC (+)000333p-SUB 111 multipolar neurons projecting V/VI (MPN proj V/VI) (active)\r\n\r\nNotes: \r\nN = 3 postweaned.\r\n\r\n'),
(6079, 636, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (-) 111021 horizontal inhibitory V (HI V) neurons', NULL, 'frozen', NULL),
(6082, 601, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)333000p-DG 1000-SUB 111 excitatory neurons', 'Pyramidal II-III (+)333000p', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis class is a merger of MEC (+)333000p-DG 1000-SUB 111 stellate II cells, EC (+)333000 principal cells, and LEC (+)333000 complex pyramidal III neurons\r\n  \r\nCross-references: to be added\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nMEC (+)333000p-DG 1000-SUB 111 stellate II cells have explicit connections to DG and SUB, whereas EC (+)333000 principal cells and LEC (+)333000 complex pyramidal III neurons only have axons that project to the angular bundle.\r\n\r\nDeep layer collaterals are attributed to Tamamaki, which is in EC (+)331111p stellate II cells.\r\n\r\nThe multiform cell does fit in this packet.  The text only description of occasional extended collaterals is insufficient to warrant a class change.\r\n\r\nAlthough Klink and Alonso''s Figures 9 and 10 appear to be the same cell, both depictions are included, since 9 depicts more of the dendritic extent and 10 depicts the axon in color for clarity.\r\n\r\nCanto 2011: LEC (+)333000 pyramidal III neurons have borderline A:IV.\r\n\r\nLingenhöhl 1991: stellate II are spiny'),
(6085, 614, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)220233p-DG 1000 pyramidal cells V-dentate gyrus projecting (PC V-DG)', 'Dentate pyramidal V (+)220233p', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis packet is a result of a merger between EC (+)220233 pyramidal V neurons, EC (+)020233p-DG 1000 pyramidal projection V neurons, and EC (+)220031 horizontal V neurons.\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nLikely excitatory cells (Lingenhohl -> spiny; Gloveli 2001 -> GABA negative, projecting, "similar EP characteristics to principal neurons"; Hamam 2002 -> projecting, sparsely spiny).\r\n\r\nThere is limited axonal info for Lingenhöhl & Finch cell 13.  L&F''s cell 10 was removed because NO axonal information is reported.\r\n\r\nLingenhöhl & Finch no longer have access to their reconstructions and could not provide the neurolucida data.\r\n\r\nGloveli''s Figure 2 is a representative example (n > 1).  D:I are borderline, which is complicated by the fact that the layer I/II border is not shown.'),
(6086, 629, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)000333p-SUB 111 multipolar neurons V/VI (MPN V-VI)', 'Multipolar V-VI (+)000333p', 'active', 'Status: active \r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis packet represents a merger between EC (+)000333p-SUB 111 multipolar projecting V neurons and EC (+)000033 multipolar-pyramid VI neurons.\r\n   \r\nNotes:  \r\nExcitatory cells (Gloveli 2001 -> GABA negative, projecting, similar EP characteristics to principal neurons; Canto & Witter 201X LEC preprint -> projecting, spiny, "principal"; Canto 2008 -> spiny, projecting).\r\n\r\nThe former 000033 class contains an unspecified axonal projection to the subiculum, and the former 000333 class is known to project to all 3 layers of the subiculum.  In 000033, evidence for axons and dendrites in IV is subthreshold, but there is a presence, so an aggressive merger was approved.\r\n'),
(6087, 638, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (-)023300 pyramid looking-bipolar neurons III (PL-BPN III)', 'Pyramidal-like III (-)023300', 'active', 'Status: active \r\n\r\nMerger status: \r\nMerger of EC (+)023300 pyramid looking III neurons and EC (+)023100 spindle III neurons\r\n   \r\nNotes: \r\nInhibitory because they have aspiny dendrites, are nonprojecting, have synapses on dendritic shafts and cell bodies, and have an indented nucleus.\r\n\r\nThese cells have a long time constant (p. 3) which is similar to Gloveli type 1 cells which are excitatory spiny pyramidal cells.\r\n\r\nBorderline \r\nDend. in L1 \r\n'),
(6092, 610, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)223200p-CA1 1000-SUB 100 pyramidal cells III (PC III)', 'Pyramidal III (+)223200p', 'active', 'Status: Active \r\n\r\nMerger status: \r\nRejected merger with EC (+)223000 Stellate III due to clear presence of D:IV in this class and unclear in stellate III.\r\n   \r\nNotes: Cell type composed of a merger of EC pyr III 223300p and EC simple pyr III 223200p\r\n'),
(6094, 608, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)231000 fan-oblique pyramidal-multipolar-pyramidal (FOMP) neurons', 'Multiform II (+)231000', 'active', 'Status: Active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis packet represents a merger between LEC (+)231000 fan-oblique pyramidal II and EC (+)231000 MPN I.\r\n\r\nFailed unofficial merger proposals with MEC 331111 stellate II, EC 331000 excitatory II, and EC 221100 oblique pyramidal-stellate II.\r\n\r\nNotes: EC (+)231000 pyramidal cells II (PC II) appended 02/15/12.\r\nSpiny, principal -> excitatory.\r\n70% of multipolar I are excitatory (Wouterlood 2000).\r\n\r\nA class of EC oblique pyramidal cells with A:I has been split off into a separate 331000 class based on a strong statement in the text about axons reaching the level of the pia with a diameter of up to 900 microm.  However, note that Figure 5 Panels A and B do not support this statement.\r\n\r\nThe second fan neuron shown in Figure 5 is included in the 331000 packet.  The text notes that axons are occasionally in deep layer I (as they are in this neuron).  However, since the 331000 packet is pre-existing, that neuron is included there in spite of the hippocampome rule about the word "occasionally."\r\n'),
(6095, 609, '2012-10-14 16:07:28', 'EC (+)223331 horizontal-bipolar-pyramidal (HOBIPPY) neurons', 'Multiform III-IV-V (+)223331', 'active', 'Status: active\r\n\r\nMerger status:\r\nThis packet is a merger of EC (+)223331 horizontal V neurons, EC (+)233331 bipolar V neurons, EC (+)223331 large pyramidal III neurons, and LEC (+)223333 large pyramidal cells V.\r\n\r\nCross-references:\r\nEC (+)333000p excitatory II \r\nEC (+)331000p excitatory II\r\nEC (+)233111 pyramidal-multiform II\r\nEC (+)231000 FOMP\r\nEC (+)000333p multipolar projection V-VI\r\n\r\nNotes:\r\nExcitatory (Lingenhöhl -> spiny; Quilichini -> principal, spiny, excitatory; Canto 2008 -> projecting; Canto 201X LEC preprint -> spiny, "principal," projecting; Tahvildari -> sparsely spiny, projecting; Canto 2011 LEC -> spiny, "principal," projecting; Canto 2008 -> spiny).\r\n\r\nNotes on EC (+)223331 horizontal V neurons\r\n- Re-added Lingenhohl & Finch cell #7 at GAA''s suggestion.  This cell \r\nwas previously mislabeled as inhibitory but is in fact excitatory based on the fact that the dendrites have spines, which is usually an indication that a cell is excitatory.\r\n- Added notes regarding A:II\r\n- Also, at the suggestion of GAA, the overall interpretation of this packet now includes D:III because of Quilichini''s Supplementary Table 1 and Lingenhohl & Finch''s cell #7, which has at-threshold presence in this layer.\r\n- Threshold: D:II and D:III\r\n\r\nNotes on EC (+)233331 bipolar V neurons\r\n- <n=4 in Canto LEC preprint>\r\n- Added Lingenhohl & Finch cell #9 (formerly classified as 223330 in suspended animation) at Giorgio''s suggestion\r\n- Threshold: A:II\r\n\r\nNotes on LEC (+)223333 large pyramidal cells V\r\n- It is unclear whether this cell type exists in MEC.');
